taking this matter seriously.

01:25.919 --> 01:28.923
I will not allow you to continue
to harass these people.

01:29.006 --> 01:30.178
Is that clear?

01:32.009 --> 01:35.138
If you violate this restraining order,
I assure you,

01:35.846 --> 01:39.191
you will spend 40 days in the county jail.

01:40.058 --> 01:40.934
I mean it.

01:41.476 --> 01:42.853
One more offense.

01:46.398 --> 01:48.070
What is obvious to this court

01:48.150 --> 01:50.614
is that you're in need of professional help

01:50.694 --> 01:52.992
and anger management counseling.

01:54.364 --> 01:57.243
This court has suggested
that you seek counseling,

01:57.326 --> 02:00.499
but since you can't
or won't do it voluntarily,

02:00.579 --> 02:03.754
I am requiring it as part
of your staying out of jail.

02:04.916 --> 02:06.793
Do I make myself clear?

02:09.211 --> 02:11.306
Do I make myself clear?

02:12.174 --> 02:13.050
Melinda?

02:14.718 --> 02:15.936
Yes, Your Honor.

02:35.113 --> 02:36.660
So,

02:37.157 --> 02:39.660
do you think you have an anger problem?

02:40.744 --> 02:43.168
Motherfucking right, I got an anger problem.

02:45.707 --> 02:49.086
Do you feel that
you're entitled to this anger?

02:53.382 --> 02:56.727
That's like asking me
if I'm entitled to being hungry.

03:01.223 --> 03:02.850
He caused all of this.

03:03.517 --> 03:04.393
All of it.

03:04.768 --> 03:07.021
It's not me. That son of a bitch owes me.

03:07.104 --> 03:08.606
What do you think he owes you?

03:08.689 --> 03:11.113
Every damn breath in his body.

03:13.402 --> 03:15.075
Why do you feel that way?

03:21.868 --> 03:23.916
You don't know what he did to me.

03:24.663 --> 03:26.085
You don't know.

03:27.666 --> 03:29.384
Would you like to share what he did?

03:30.127 --> 03:31.754
Do I have a choice?

03:32.421 --> 03:34.765
We all have choices.

03:35.590 --> 03:38.890
Not when some damn judge
is making me sit here.

03:41.138 --> 03:44.859
- You know what?
- This is bullshit, okay?

03:50.439 --> 03:55.411
This motherfucker torments me,
and he gets to walk away free.

04:01.491 --> 04:03.038
What are you writing?

04:03.118 --> 04:04.290
Just my notes.

04:05.662 --> 04:07.460
And what do your notes say?

04:09.875 --> 04:11.422
I'm a stereotype?

04:12.961 --> 04:14.964
Is that what you think you are?

04:15.046 --> 04:16.047
Hell, no!

04:19.384 --> 04:21.682
Sick and tired of hearing that.

04:23.263 --> 04:26.608
Every time a black woman gets mad,
she's a stereotype.

04:27.267 --> 04:30.357
"Ooh, she emasculates men."

04:30.437 --> 04:32.275
Is that what you think you did?

04:32.355 --> 04:33.197
Bitch...

04:34.107 --> 04:36.030
are you not listening to me?

04:37.694 --> 04:40.448
I never did anything to him.

04:44.659 --> 04:47.083
I was everything he needed me to be.

04:49.414 --> 04:50.256
I was...

04:52.459 --> 04:55.133
I was strong when he needed me to be.

04:55.712 --> 04:58.966
I played weak when he needed me to.

05:00.592 --> 05:02.139
I was pathetic.

05:06.598 --> 05:07.440
I was...

05:16.274 --> 05:19.028
Don't tell me I don't have
a right to be angry. Hmm?

05:19.778 --> 05:21.906
Is that what you think I said?

05:23.240 --> 05:25.243
I really don't give a damn what you said.

05:25.325 --> 05:26.496
But this is wrong.

05:26.576 --> 05:28.290
All of this is wrong.

05:28.370 --> 05:30.247
Why don't we do this?

05:30.872 --> 05:32.875
Why don't we just start from the beginning?

05:34.501 --> 05:36.504
Help me understand this injustice.

05:36.586 --> 05:38.384
Just tell me what happened.

05:44.678 --> 05:45.896
How far back do you wanna go?

05:49.516 --> 05:51.234
I remember every damn day.

05:53.562 --> 05:54.689
That's the problem.

05:55.897 --> 05:57.360
Can't forget it.

05:57.440 --> 06:00.239
I can't get it out of my head.

06:01.987 --> 06:02.829
So...

06:05.323 --> 06:07.075
How far do you wanna go?

06:08.368 --> 06:10.336
Well, let's start at the beginning.

06:12.372 --> 06:13.214
Okay.

06:13.456 --> 06:14.920
How'd you meet him?

06:15.000 --> 06:16.422
It was raining.

06:19.129 --> 06:20.847
<i>I was in college...</i>

06:21.715 --> 06:23.934
<i>and I was studying late.</i>

06:24.426 --> 06:26.269
<i>It was raining really hard.</i>

06:27.012 --> 06:30.266
<i>I don't know.
Crazy shit happens to me in the rain.</i>

06:30.724 --> 06:32.021
<i>Around water.</i>

06:33.435 --> 06:37.484
<i>I was trying to get back to my dorm,
and I ran into him.</i>

06:37.564 --> 06:39.191
- No!
- Damn!

06:39.274 --> 06:41.112
- No, no!
- You can't watch what you're doing?

06:41.192 --> 06:43.695
Move! You the idiot who bumped into me!

06:45.196 --> 06:46.618
Girl, what's wrong with you?

06:49.409 --> 06:50.251
Damn!

06:58.168 --> 06:59.169
Hi.

06:59.252 --> 07:00.845
Is Melissa here?

07:01.838 --> 07:03.431
There's no Melissa here.

07:04.090 --> 07:05.929
Oh, Melinda. Melinda's...

07:06.009 --> 07:07.180
What do you want?

07:07.260 --> 07:08.978
- Who's this?
- The asshole.

07:09.804 --> 07:11.476
I'm sorry. Here.

07:11.556 --> 07:12.808
I have some of your papers.

07:12.891 --> 07:14.689
Great. Just great.

07:16.144 --> 07:17.941
And I think you may have one or two of mine.

07:18.021 --> 07:19.989
No, I don't. Sorry.

07:21.066 --> 07:24.195
Here. Forgive her.
She's really bad at history,

07:24.277 --> 07:26.075
- and she had a paper to turn in today...
- Sarah!

07:27.489 --> 07:28.365
Goodbye.

07:28.698 --> 07:30.912
Look, I feel really bad
about bumping into you.

07:30.992 --> 07:33.586
I can be in my own head
when I'm working on a project.

07:34.204 --> 07:35.205
I'm sorry.

07:35.288 --> 07:36.459
Okay, yeah. Fine.

07:36.539 --> 07:38.128
But if you don't mind now,

07:38.208 --> 07:40.336
I have less than 24 hours to finish my paper.

07:40.418 --> 07:41.465
So, goodbye.

07:41.836 --> 07:44.551
Well, your basis is way off
in the first four pages,

07:44.631 --> 07:47.178
and the facts of
the Spanish-American War are wrong.

07:47.258 --> 07:49.477
And Professor Huff
will catch that in a second.

07:50.470 --> 07:51.558
How do you know that?

07:51.638 --> 07:53.185
I took his class last year.

07:54.474 --> 07:55.942
I'm sorry for reading your first pages.

07:57.352 --> 07:59.025
I got an A in his class.

07:59.771 --> 08:01.569
I can help you if you'd like.

08:02.774 --> 08:05.903
<i>I was so mad the first time I saw him</i>

08:05.986 --> 08:09.034
<i>that I didn't even realize
how handsome he was.</i>

08:09.114 --> 08:10.241
Please?

08:10.323 --> 08:12.162
<i>He was beautiful. Gotta give him that.</i>

08:12.242 --> 08:15.916
<i>The devil sure knows
how to put a package together.</i>

08:15.996 --> 08:20.045
<i>Standing in front of me
was all the things I loved.</i>

08:20.125 --> 08:22.753
<i>He was dark, sexy.</i>

08:23.378 --> 08:25.051
- It was 1497.
- No.

08:25.380 --> 08:27.383
Look, this is too hard for me to remember.

08:27.465 --> 08:28.511
Can we take a break?

08:28.591 --> 08:30.468
I don't wanna talk about this stuff anymore.

08:30.552 --> 08:31.679
You don't have much time.

08:31.761 --> 08:33.683
It's too much, okay?

08:33.763 --> 08:36.562
I'm on a brain overload.

08:37.142 --> 08:39.440
So, let's talk about you.

08:40.145 --> 08:43.443
Those papers you needed, what were they?

08:43.523 --> 08:44.445
Tell me.

08:44.774 --> 08:47.027
I think I've found a solution
to an age-old problem.

08:47.861 --> 08:49.989
I'm creating a battery
that can recharge itself.

08:50.947 --> 08:55.246
If it works, it can be used in cars,
homes, you name it.

08:55.326 --> 08:57.248
And I'm gonna be so rich.

08:57.328 --> 08:59.042
While saving the environment, of course.

08:59.122 --> 09:00.795
Of course.

09:02.167 --> 09:04.010
<i>He was so charming.</i>

09:04.461 --> 09:06.134
<i>So slick.</i>

09:06.880 --> 09:08.426
<i>I just wish to high heaven</i>

09:08.506 --> 09:12.261
<i>someone would have said to me
right then and there,</i>

09:12.343 --> 09:14.846
<i>"Girl, get up and run as fast as you can</i>

09:14.929 --> 09:18.728
<i>because this man will leave you devastated."</i>

09:18.808 --> 09:20.026
How'd you do?

09:20.351 --> 09:21.193
Tell me.

09:23.813 --> 09:25.065
But we studied.

09:25.148 --> 09:26.194
Yo, I'm sorry.

09:26.274 --> 09:27.988
Let me talk to Professor Huff.
Maybe we get you a make-up.

09:28.068 --> 09:29.195
No. No, okay?

09:29.277 --> 09:32.201
I mean, this is all just a waste of money.

09:33.239 --> 09:35.537
I can't keep doing this to my mother.

09:36.284 --> 09:37.661
To be honest with you, I mean,

09:37.744 --> 09:40.122
she was surprised I was even going to school.

09:40.872 --> 09:42.749
I wasn't as smart as my sisters.

09:44.626 --> 09:45.593
Come here.

09:50.131 --> 09:51.007
Melinda.

09:53.468 --> 09:55.971
Hey, what are you doing here?

09:56.054 --> 09:57.475
Mama...

09:57.555 --> 10:01.104
<i>My sisters came to tell me
that my mother had died.</i>

10:02.852 --> 10:05.525
<i>My mother and I always been close.</i>

10:05.605 --> 10:08.859
May she rest in peace. Amen.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.444
<i>I was numb.</i>

10:10.527 --> 10:12.996
<i>I was so desperate to feel anything.</i>

10:14.072 --> 10:15.449
<i>You see, that's how this happened.</i>

10:15.532 --> 10:19.162
<i>He was there at the right time
to take advantage of me.</i>

10:28.753 --> 10:29.716
Hi.

10:29.796 --> 10:30.967
I'm Brenda.

10:31.047 --> 10:32.299
Hey, I'm Robert.

10:32.841 --> 10:34.343
You have a last name?

10:34.425 --> 10:35.513
Gayle.

10:35.593 --> 10:37.345
- Hmm.
- How do you know Melinda?

10:38.721 --> 10:40.724
- School.
- Oh.

10:40.807 --> 10:42.729
Well, we haven't seen you around here.

10:42.809 --> 10:44.898
Yeah, I'm from Kirkwood.

10:44.978 --> 10:45.945
Oh.

10:46.604 --> 10:48.823
Well, this is a different side
of the tracks for you.

10:49.649 --> 10:51.117
What do you do for a living?

10:51.734 --> 10:53.073
I'm in school right now.

10:53.153 --> 10:55.116
Oh. That's good. That's good.

10:55.196 --> 10:56.038
Yeah.

10:57.824 --> 11:00.248
Well, if you don't have a job,
then who's paying for it?

11:01.744 --> 11:04.042
Student loans. Scholarships.

11:04.122 --> 11:05.249
That kind of thing.

11:05.331 --> 11:06.252
Oh. So you must be smart.

11:06.332 --> 11:07.629
Or an athlete.

11:08.001 --> 11:10.095
- No, no athlete.
- No? Oh.

11:11.629 --> 11:13.843
Oh. This is my boyfriend, Casey.

11:13.923 --> 11:15.637
- Oh. Hi.
- Hi, man.

11:15.717 --> 11:17.055
- Hey. Nice to meet you, man.
- Good to meet you, too.

11:17.135 --> 11:18.848
And this is Kalvin, Brenda's fiancé.

11:18.928 --> 11:20.100
- What's up, man?
- Good to meet you.

11:20.180 --> 11:21.351
Good to meet you as well.

11:21.431 --> 11:22.977
So what are you studying?

11:23.057 --> 11:24.434
Mechanical engineering.

11:24.517 --> 11:26.564
- Oh. Devon, come here.
- Hey.

11:26.644 --> 11:27.982
Hey.

11:28.062 --> 11:29.150
Sorry about your mom.

11:29.230 --> 11:30.276
Thank you so much.

11:30.356 --> 11:32.278
- How are you?
- I'm good.

11:32.358 --> 11:33.985
Oh. I'm so rude. Um...

11:34.068 --> 11:35.532
What's your name again?

11:35.612 --> 11:36.454
Robert.

11:36.946 --> 11:38.409
Robert. Robert, this is Devon.

11:38.489 --> 11:40.286
Devon, this is Robert.

11:40.366 --> 11:42.744
- Devon is Melinda's boyfriend.
- Nice to meet you.

11:43.620 --> 11:44.872
Ex-boyfriend.

11:44.954 --> 11:47.043
- You know she still loves you.
- Mmm-hmm.

11:47.123 --> 11:49.091
Oh, Mel, look who came!

11:49.876 --> 11:50.798
Hey.

11:51.544 --> 11:53.091
I'm sorry about your mom.

11:53.171 --> 11:54.509
Thank you.

11:54.589 --> 11:57.217
Oh, uh, Devon, come with me for a second.

11:57.300 --> 11:58.677
Melinda, we have to thank the pastor.

11:59.219 --> 12:01.182
- You know him, right?
- Okay. Yeah, yeah.

12:01.262 --> 12:03.230
- I'll be right back, okay?
- Okay.

12:19.030 --> 12:19.872
Robert!

12:20.490 --> 12:22.083
- Hey.
- Hey.

12:22.909 --> 12:24.502
Why are you leaving so soon?

12:25.245 --> 12:26.372
Well, you have your family.

12:26.454 --> 12:28.172
I just wanted to make sure that you're okay.

12:31.084 --> 12:32.051
Thank you.

12:32.377 --> 12:33.378
Yeah.

12:34.796 --> 12:35.797
Of course.

12:39.300 --> 12:40.802
I'll see you later, all right?

12:40.885 --> 12:42.853
Wait, where are you going?

12:44.639 --> 12:45.686
To the train.

12:46.891 --> 12:48.980
The train? I mean, that's a long way.

12:49.060 --> 12:50.312
Did you walk here?

12:50.395 --> 12:51.858
You walked here? Look, no, I can just...

12:51.938 --> 12:53.065
- No, I'm fine. I'm fine.
- I can drive you.

12:53.147 --> 12:54.319
No, no, look. I'll get my keys.

12:54.399 --> 12:56.112
I'll be right back, I'll drive you.

12:56.192 --> 12:57.410
Mel. Melin...

13:03.408 --> 13:05.126
Wow, is that your house?

13:06.536 --> 13:08.379
No. That's my house.

13:11.165 --> 13:12.542
You live in there?

13:12.959 --> 13:13.801
Yeah.

13:15.461 --> 13:16.679
Can I come in?

13:18.381 --> 13:19.223
Yeah.

13:26.264 --> 13:27.265
Watch your step.

13:27.348 --> 13:28.315
Thank you.

13:39.444 --> 13:41.196
What kind of music is this?

13:42.613 --> 13:43.831
Are you kidding me?

13:44.449 --> 13:45.325
What?

13:45.700 --> 13:47.168
This is Nina Simone.

13:47.994 --> 13:49.621
You've never heard of her?

13:50.163 --> 13:51.540
No.

13:51.622 --> 13:53.670
I need to play something
for you then. Hold on.

13:53.750 --> 13:55.421
- I'll pass.
- No, no, no.

13:55.501 --> 13:56.798
You have to hear her voice.

13:56.878 --> 13:58.676
Her singing is like going to church.

14:00.256 --> 14:01.094
Listen.

14:07.096 --> 14:08.598
It's kind of sad.

14:09.515 --> 14:11.142
- I'm so sorry.
- No, no, no. It's fine.

14:11.225 --> 14:12.226
You can leave it on.

14:18.107 --> 14:20.201
So how long have you lived here?

14:21.277 --> 14:22.199
A while.

14:23.654 --> 14:26.908
I know it's not much,
but my uncle left it to me,

14:26.991 --> 14:29.961
and my aunt lets me stay here
in the driveway for free.

14:31.913 --> 14:33.165
Where are your parents?

14:33.873 --> 14:35.125
My father's in prison.

14:36.000 --> 14:37.627
And my mother left me with my grandmother,

14:37.710 --> 14:40.179
who raised me until she died, when I was 14.

14:42.673 --> 14:46.803
Then I moved out here with my aunt,
and I've been living out here ever since.

14:51.015 --> 14:52.437
I'm sorry to hear about your mother.

14:53.684 --> 14:55.273
She sounded like a good lady.

14:55.353 --> 14:56.195
Yeah.

14:56.687 --> 14:59.782
Yeah, she was amazing.

15:00.942 --> 15:02.489
You know, she...

15:03.986 --> 15:05.113
It's okay.

15:06.280 --> 15:07.247
Come here.

15:11.536 --> 15:12.503
I'm sorry.

15:12.954 --> 15:15.251
<i>There was something about
the way he said he was sorry</i>

15:15.331 --> 15:16.674
<i>that made me believe it.</i>

15:16.999 --> 15:18.626
<i>And the way he held me.</i>

15:19.085 --> 15:20.882
<i>I know this sounds so stupid,</i>

15:20.962 --> 15:24.091
<i>but you have to know, I was a kid.</i>

15:24.173 --> 15:27.803
<i>He made me feel safe and strong and...</i>

15:27.885 --> 15:29.057
You're beautiful.

15:29.137 --> 15:30.229
<i>...beautiful.</i>

15:30.721 --> 15:33.475
<i>My mother wasn't even cold in the ground yet,</i>

15:33.558 --> 15:34.980
<i>and there I was.</i>

15:36.519 --> 15:39.734
<i>What kind of man takes advantage
of a girl's grief, huh?</i>

15:39.814 --> 15:40.815
<i>I'll tell you.</i>

15:40.898 --> 15:44.697
<i>A low-life maggot of a motherfucker,
that's who.</i>

15:44.777 --> 15:48.076
<i>He had to know that grief can leave you open</i>

15:48.156 --> 15:50.495
<i>to not knowing yourself at all.</i>

15:50.575 --> 15:53.203
<i>Add that to me being so young.</i>

15:53.619 --> 15:57.089
<i>He had my mind, my heart, my head...</i>

15:57.582 --> 15:59.420
<i>and, let's not forget...</i>

15:59.500 --> 16:00.797
<i>my virginity.</i>

16:23.316 --> 16:25.694
Oh. What are you listening to in here?

16:25.776 --> 16:27.779
You never heard of Nina Simone?

16:27.862 --> 16:29.659
Oh. That's Mama's music.

16:29.739 --> 16:31.241
Or it's that boy's.

16:34.327 --> 16:36.045
You going out with him again?

16:37.038 --> 16:38.000
Yeah.

16:38.080 --> 16:40.708
And I wish you would stop saying "him."

16:41.292 --> 16:45.341
His name is Robert,
and I really like him, okay?

16:45.421 --> 16:47.173
And I want you to like him, too.

16:47.256 --> 16:49.759
Are you having sex with him?

16:52.470 --> 16:53.972
Well, it's a fair question.

16:54.055 --> 16:55.648
But what I wanna know is,

16:56.724 --> 16:59.352
who's paying when
y'all going out on all these dates?

17:00.937 --> 17:01.779
What?

17:02.647 --> 17:04.115
Look, Melinda.

17:04.690 --> 17:05.987
Don't tell that boy

17:06.067 --> 17:08.069
that Mama left you that money and this house.

17:08.152 --> 17:10.119
- I'm telling you.
- All right.

17:13.699 --> 17:16.953
<i>Ugh. I hate to admit it,
but Brenda was right.</i>

17:18.371 --> 17:21.669
<i>I had made the mistake
of telling Robert about the house</i>

17:21.749 --> 17:25.049
<i>and the $350,000 that my mom left me.</i>

17:25.752 --> 17:27.800
<i>But that didn't matter to him, right?</i>

17:28.339 --> 17:29.557
<i>He wanted me.</i>

17:30.216 --> 17:31.058
<i>Right?</i>

17:31.509 --> 17:34.182
So the name of the company is called
Prescott & Howard Industries.

17:34.262 --> 17:35.099
Okay.

17:35.179 --> 17:38.728
And the owner, David Prescott,
is a super cool guy.

17:38.808 --> 17:41.687
Man, he's always looking
for the next big thing.

17:42.937 --> 17:44.564
And he's a tree-hugger billionaire

17:44.647 --> 17:46.569
always talking about
saving the environment, you know?

17:46.649 --> 17:48.821
So he finds people who just have great ideas

17:48.901 --> 17:51.700
and he changes their lives.

17:52.822 --> 17:55.200
You know, he's made millionaires
out of a lot of people

17:55.283 --> 17:57.705
just by investing in their project.

17:57.785 --> 17:59.081
And it's a lottery.

17:59.161 --> 18:02.084
He goes through the mail and finds ideas.

18:02.164 --> 18:04.837
But if he likes them,
then he contacts you for a meeting,

18:04.917 --> 18:08.341
and you have to come right when he says come,

18:08.421 --> 18:10.384
which is pretty cool.

18:10.464 --> 18:12.341
So I send a letter to his office every week

18:12.425 --> 18:14.514
talking about my battery idea.

18:14.594 --> 18:16.062
You know what I call it?

